y88e ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">If we are following Christ, why is it impossible for anyone, </div><div class="t m430 x84 h13 y546 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">including Satan, to condemn us? </div><div class="t m24c x77 h13 y88f ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What does it mean that &quot;in all these things [vs. 37] we are more </div><div class="t m30c x84 h13 y890 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">than conquerors&quot;? </div><div class="t m6d3 x77 h13 y891 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What does it mean that Christ is making intercession for us? </div><div class="t m192 x84 h13 y892 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(vs. 34). How should that reality impact how we live? Why do we </div><div class="t m4a0 x84 h13 y893 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">need an intercessor? </div><div class="t m228 x77 h13 y894 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, </div><div class="t m6e1 x2d h13 y895 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nor principalities, nor powers, nor things present, nor things to </div><div class="t m4ef x2d h13 y896 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">come, nor height, nor depth, nor any other creature, shall be </div><div class="t m549 x2d h13 y897 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ </div><div class="t md2 x2d h13 y898 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus our Lord&quot; (vss. 38, 39). What do these words mean, par-</div><div class="t m6e2 x2d h13 y899 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ticularly in the context of the great controversy? What assur-</div><div class="t m60c x2d h13 y89a ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ance can we draw from them? At the same time, what don&apos;t they </div><div class="t m6e3 x2d h13 y89b ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mean? What false conclusions can someone draw from them </div><div class="t m451 x2d h13 y89c ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">regarding salvation? </div><div class="t m624 x1f h13 y86f ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In the midst of these wonderful promises, Paul inserts these </div><div class="t m646 x1e h13 y89d ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">words: &quot;For thy sake we are killed all the day long; we are </div><div class="t m74 x1e h13 y89e ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">accounted as sheep for the slaughter&quot; (vs. 36). What is he talking </div><div class="t m6e4 x1e h13 y89f ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">about here? How does this fit in with the rest of the verses? </div><div class="t m146 x1e h13 y8a0 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Hint: See verse 37. </div><div class="t mcf x9b h15 y8a1 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">93 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
